%section.main
  %section
    .home-top
      %div.container
        %section.contain-centered
          %h1.home-top-header exercism.io
          %h2.home-top-subheader The Devil is in the Details
          %p.lead.home Crowd-sourced mentorship. Public prototype.
          %a.btn.btn-large.btn-success.home{href: '/login'} Start Now (via GitHub)

%div.container
  %section.content-primary.home
    %div.row
      %div.span4
        %img.medallion{:src => link_to("/icons/badge-iteration.svg")}
        %h2.header Practice
        %p.contain-centered
          %span.home-third-subheader
            Focus on expressive, readable code.

        %p.home-p-text
          Work in your local development environment using your usual tools
          = succeed "." do
            %a{:href => link_to('/about')} in multiple languages
          We give you a test suite, and you make the tests pass... but that's just the first step.

      %div.span4
        %img.medallion{:src => link_to("/icons/badge-people.svg")}
        %h2.header Communicate
        %p.contain-centered
          %span.home-third-subheader
            The code is a conversation starter.
        %p.home-p-text
          Have a thoughtful discussion with your peers about the choices that you made. Take this opportunity to explore idioms, style, and trade-offs.  There's no right answer, and many good questions.

      %div.span4
        %img.medallion{:src => link_to("/icons/badge-nitpick.svg")}
        %h2.header Pay it Forward
        %p.contain-centered
          %span.home-third-subheader
            Explore other people's solutions.
        %p.home-p-text
          Articulate what you like and dislike in other people's code. Have a thoughtful, nuanced discussion, deepening your own understanding of the design choices that you make every day.

  %section.content-secondary.see-it
    %div.row
      %div.span6
        %h3.header Better code through conversations.
        %p.home-p-text Thousands of conversations are happening on exercism. <a href="/conversations/1">Here's one of them.</a>
        %p.home-p-text You start with some code.  Talk about it a little.  Rewrite the code a bit, then post the new version.  Make it better.  After a few cycles you've got improved code, and perhaps even a new friend!

      %div.span6
        %a(href="/conversations/1")
          %img{:src => link_to("/img/conversation.jpg"), alt: "Exercism code conversation."}

  %section.content-secondary
    %div.row
      %div.span6
        %div.content-secondary-details
          %h2 Try it.
          %p.home-p-text You don't need to log in to check out the problems. Go to a temporary directory.
          %pre $ cd /tmp
          %p.home-p-text
            Download the
            = succeed "," do
              %a(href="https://github.com/exercism/cli/releases/latest") command line client
            unpack it.
          %p.home-p-text The binary is named <kbd>exercism</kbd>. Fetch the first exercise available for each language:
          %pre $ ./exercism demo

      %div.span6
        %img{:src => link_to("/img/home-try-it.png"), alt: ""}
